snippet.title: [FULL] Fukashigi no Carte - Seishun Buta Yarou wa Bunny Girl Senpai no Yume wo Minai ED [Synthesia]
snippet.description:
After a bit of pain trying to write variations, I'm finally finished full version of Fukashigi no Carte, ED to SeiButa!

I can rant forever about how amazing the anime is, or how weird the song was for me to arrange, but I won't. If you want to argue or talk with me about this, I'm always on Twitter and Discord!
 That's how much of a fan I am on this anime, I'm willing to yell anyone else down if they even say it's remotely bad.

The song itself is amazing too. The variations of the chorus is minimal, but I managed to write unique runs for each one. The piano solo/improv in the middle I just copied, and I also copied the original ending I had on my TV-size. For the half-step modulation, I just did a direct modulation via a pivot note of F.

Yea it was a pain to arrange. At least it turned out okay!

Enjoy!

P.S. don't ask me who best girl is, I can't decide.

EDIT: Thank you to @HalcyonMusic for playing my arrangement! Now I know it's not impossible :)
Link here: https://youtu.be/nS2glOKg0Do
Show him some love!
